{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/2011/09/osx-lion-reverse-scrolling","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Kevin McKelvin"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e6ac13be-43d9-58b9-b1ed-95021f41c043","excerpt":"The subject of mouse movement in OS X has been debated for years now.  Personally I despise the default movement settings in OS X and have a whole array of…","html":"<p>The subject of mouse movement in OS X has been debated for years now.  Personally I despise the default movement settings in OS X and have a whole array of tweaks in place.  But that’s a debate for another day.</p>\n<p>Today I’m looking at the new “natural” reversed scrolling feature in Lion.  Having used it for a couple of days now I found that I like having the reverse scrolling on the trackpad, but whenever I reach for my mouse I prefer the classic scrolling method that we’ve been using for years.</p>\n<p>I dug around and couldn’t find any way inside OS X of decoupling them, but I came across a cool app called <a href=\"http://pilotmoon.com/scrollreverser/\">Scroll Reverser</a>.  It allows you to customize the reverse scrolling of the track pad and not of the mouse.</p>\n<p>The settings might seem a bit confusing though.  I have OSX set up to reverse scrolling so that it works across all applications.  I then use Scroll Reverser to reverse the scrolling on the mouse from OSX’s behaviour back to the classic behaviour.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 360px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/230e9233b602eabcc4e1482080f9e733/34b33/110921_scrollreverser_settings.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67.22222222222223%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Scroll Reverser Settings\"\n        title=\"Scroll Reverser Settings\"\n        src=\"/static/230e9233b602eabcc4e1482080f9e733/34b33/110921_scrollreverser_settings.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/230e9233b602eabcc4e1482080f9e733/00d96/110921_scrollreverser_settings.png 148w,\n/static/230e9233b602eabcc4e1482080f9e733/0b23c/110921_scrollreverser_settings.png 295w,\n/static/230e9233b602eabcc4e1482080f9e733/34b33/110921_scrollreverser_settings.png 360w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/311c913a5857981bb693fb15f08a39ae/7d484/110921_mouse_pref.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.12220566318926%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Preferences\"\n        title=\"Preferences\"\n        src=\"/static/311c913a5857981bb693fb15f08a39ae/799d3/110921_mouse_pref.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/311c913a5857981bb693fb15f08a39ae/00d96/110921_mouse_pref.png 148w,\n/static/311c913a5857981bb693fb15f08a39ae/0b23c/110921_mouse_pref.png 295w,\n/static/311c913a5857981bb693fb15f08a39ae/799d3/110921_mouse_pref.png 590w,\n/static/311c913a5857981bb693fb15f08a39ae/7d484/110921_mouse_pref.png 671w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    <